{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YWKh38fbHsxwHNSAPKt6Cz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed report of the entire project structure.\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE EXPLORATION REPORT: ralph-burning-rewrite\n\nI've thoroughly explored the ralph-burning-rewrite project. Here's a complete picture of what's implemented:\n\n---\n\n### 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE - src/ DIRECTORIES\n\nThe project is organized into 5 main directories under `src/`:\n\n**`src/cli/`** - CLI Command Handlers (8 modules)\n- `init.rs` - Initialize workspace\n- `flow.rs` - List/show flow presets\n- `config.rs` - Manage workspace configuration\n- `project.rs` - Create/select/list/delete/show projects\n- `run.rs` - Start/resume/status/history/tail/rollback runs\n- `requirements.rs` - Draft requirements, answer questions\n- `daemon.rs` - Manage automation daemon (start, status, abort, retry, reconcile)\n- `conformance.rs` - Run conformance tests\n- `mod.rs` - CLI routing (8 commands)\n\n**`src/contexts/`** - 6 Bounded Contexts (DDD architecture)\n- `agent_execution/` - AI backend invocation\n- `automation_runtime/` - Daemon-based task execution\n- `conformance_spec/` - Behavioral test specifications\n- `project_run_record/` - Workflow execution state management\n- `requirements_drafting/` - Interactive requirements gathering\n- `workflow_composition/` - Flow definitions and orchestration\n- `workspace_governance/` - Workspace initialization and config\n\n**`src/adapters/`** - Infrastructure Adapters (4 modules)\n- `fs.rs` - Filesystem-based storage (15 store implementations)\n- `stub_backend.rs` - In-memory AI backend for testing\n- `worktree.rs` - Git worktree management\n- `mod.rs` - Module declaration\n\n**`src/shared/`** - Shared Kernel\n- `domain.rs` - Core domain types\n- `error.rs` - Error handling\n- `mod.rs` - Module declaration\n\n---\n\n### 2. BOUNDED CONTEXTS - DETAILED VIEW\n\n#### **agent_execution** - AI Backend Execution\nFiles: `model.rs`, `service.rs`, `session.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Abstract layer for LLM backend invocations\n- **Key Types**:\n  - `InvocationContract` - Stage execution contract\n  - `InvocationPayload` - Stage input/output data\n  - `AgentExecutionService` - Executes stage invocations\n  - `SessionManager` - Manages LLM session reuse\n- **Features**:\n  - Backend selection (Claude, Codex, OpenRouter, Stub)\n  - Structured output validation\n  - Raw output capture\n  - Session persistence\n\n#### **automation_runtime** - Daemon-Based Task Processing\nFiles: `daemon_loop.rs`, `lease_service.rs`, `model.rs`, `routing.rs`, `task_service.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Long-running daemon that claims and processes tasks\n- **Key Types**:\n  - `DaemonTask` - Task with status, lease, and metadata\n  - `WorktreeLease` - Git worktree ownership tracking\n  - `DaemonLoop` - Main polling loop\n  - `LeaseService` - Lease management and reconciliation\n  - `RoutingEngine` - Route tasks to worktrees\n- **Task Statuses**: Pending → Claimed → Active → (Completed/Failed/Aborted)\n- **Ports**:\n  - `DaemonStorePort` - Task and lease persistence\n  - `WorktreePort` - Git worktree operations\n\n#### **conformance_spec** - Behavioral Test Framework\nFiles: `catalog.rs`, `cutover_guard.rs`, `model.rs`, `runner.rs`, `scenarios.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Cucumber-based conformance test execution\n- **Key Components**:\n  - Feature file discovery from `tests/conformance/features/`\n  - Scenario registration and filtering\n  - Test runner with reporter\n  - Cutover guard validation\n\n#### **project_run_record** - Run State Management\nFiles: `journal.rs`, `model.rs`, `queries.rs`, `service.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Durable state tracking for workflow execution\n- **Key Types**:\n  - `ProjectRecord` - Canonical project metadata\n  - `RunSnapshot` - Current execution state\n  - `JournalEvent` - Immutable event log\n  - `Payload` - Stage input/output artifacts\n  - `RollbackPoint` - Checkpoint for recovery\n- **Ports**:\n  - `ProjectStorePort` - Project metadata persistence\n  - `RunSnapshotPort` - Execution state queries/writes\n  - `JournalStorePort` - Event log persistence\n  - `ArtifactStorePort` - Payload/artifact storage\n\n#### **requirements_drafting** - Interactive Requirements\nFiles: `contracts.rs`, `model.rs`, `renderers.rs`, `service.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Gather requirements through Q&A dialogue\n- **Key Types**:\n  - `QuestionSet` - Multiple choice/open questions\n  - `AnswerCollection` - User responses\n  - `ProjectSeed` - Generated project template\n- **Modes**: Draft (interactive), Quick (automated with stub)\n- **Output**: Generates seed prompt and project configuration\n\n#### **workflow_composition** - Flow Orchestration\nFiles: `contracts.rs`, `engine.rs`, `payloads.rs`, `renderers.rs`, `retry_policy.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Define and execute multi-stage workflows\n- **Key Concepts**:\n  - `FlowDefinition` - Stage sequence + validation profile\n  - `FlowSemantics` - Flow-specific logic (planning, execution, remediation)\n  - `RetryPolicy` - Failure recovery strategy\n  - Cycle-based execution (multiple attempts through remediation)\n  - Amendment queue for deferred changes\n- **Main Functions**:\n  - `execute_run()` - Run all stages from start\n  - `resume_run()` - Resume from failed/paused state\n  - Cycle management and completion rounds\n\n#### **workspace_governance** - Configuration & Initialization\nFiles: `config.rs`, `mod.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Workspace and project configuration management\n- **Key Features**:\n  - Workspace initialization with version 1\n  - Config loading/saving (TOML-based)\n  - Active project tracking\n  - Configuration keys: `prompt_review.enabled`, `default_flow`, `default_backend`, `default_model`\n- **Directory Structure**:\n  ```\n  .ralph-burning/\n    workspace.toml\n    active-project\n    projects/{project-id}/\n      project.toml\n      prompt.md\n      run.json\n      journal.ndjson\n      sessions.json\n      history/{payloads,artifacts}/\n      runtime/{logs,backend,temp}/\n      amendments/\n      rollback/\n    requirements/\n    daemon/\n      tasks/\n      leases/\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### 3. ADAPTER MODULES - IMPLEMENTATIONS\n\n#### **fs.rs** (1,538 lines) - Filesystem Storage Adapters\nImplements 15 store ports for durable storage:\n\n**Project Management Stores**:\n- `FsProjectStore` - ProjectStorePort\n- `FsActiveProjectStore` - ActiveProjectPort\n\n**Execution State Stores**:\n- `FsRunSnapshotStore` - RunSnapshotPort (read-only)\n- `FsRunSnapshotWriteStore` - RunSnapshotWritePort\n- `FsJournalStore` - JournalStorePort\n\n**Payload & Artifact Stores**:\n- `FsArtifactStore` - ArtifactStorePort\n- `FsPayloadArtifactWriteStore` - PayloadArtifactWritePort\n- `FsRollbackPointStore` - RollbackPointStorePort\n\n**Backend Output Stores**:\n- `FsRawOutputStore` - RawOutputPort\n- `FsSessionStore` - SessionStorePort\n- `FsRuntimeLogStore` - RuntimeLogStorePort\n- `FsRuntimeLogWriteStore` - RuntimeLogWritePort\n\n**Daemon Stores**:\n- `FsDaemonStore` - DaemonStorePort (tasks, leases, journal, locks)\n- `FsAmendmentQueueStore` - AmendmentQueuePort\n\n**Requirements Stores**:\n- `FsRequirementsStore` - RequirementsStorePort\n\n**FileSystem Utilities**:\n- Static methods for: workspace init, TOML rendering, file I/O, editor invocation\n\n#### **stub_backend.rs** (414 lines) - Test AI Backend\n- In-memory LLM simulation for testing\n- Environment variable injection seams for failure modes:\n  - `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_BACKEND_UNAVAILABLE` - Simulate unavailable backend\n  - `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_FAIL_INVOKE_STAGE` - Fail specific stage invocation\n  - `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_TRANSIENT_FAILURE` - Transient N-attempt failures\n  - `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_STAGE_OVERRIDES` - Custom payloads per stage\n  - `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_LABEL_OVERRIDES` - Custom requirement responses\n\n#### **worktree.rs** (198 lines) - Git Worktree Management\n- Create/remove worktrees in `.ralph-burning/daemon/worktrees/{task-id}/`\n- Branch naming based on task ID\n- Rebase onto default branch\n- Shell-based git operations\n\n---\n\n### 4. CLI COMMAND STRUCTURE\n\n**Main CLI (defined in `src/cli/mod.rs`)**:\n\n```\nralph-burning [SUBCOMMAND]\n├── init                         - Initialize workspace\n├── flow\n│   ├── list                     - List all flow presets\n│   └── show <flow_id>           - Show flow details\n├── config\n│   ├── show                     - Display all configuration\n│   ├── get <key>                - Get single config value\n│   ├── set <key> <value>        - Set config value\n│   └── edit                     - Edit workspace.toml in editor\n├── project\n│   ├── create --id <ID> --name <NAME> --prompt <PATH> --flow <FLOW>\n│   ├── select <ID>              - Set active project\n│   ├── list                     - List all projects\n│   ├── show [<ID>]              - Show project details (active if not specified)\n│   └── delete <ID>              - Delete project\n├── run\n│   ├── start                    - Execute all stages of active project\n│   ├── resume                   - Resume from failed/paused snapshot\n│   ├── status                   - Show current execution status\n│   ├── history                  - Show all journal events and payloads\n│   ├── tail [--logs]            - Show recent events and optional runtime logs\n│   └── rollback --to <STAGE> [--hard]  - Rollback to stage\n├── requirements\n│   ├── draft --idea <IDEA>      - Interactive requirements gathering\n│   ├── quick --idea <IDEA>      - Automated requirements (stub backend)\n│   ├── show <RUN_ID>            - Display requirements result\n│   └── answer <RUN_ID>          - Submit answers to pending questions\n├── daemon\n│   ├── start [--poll-seconds N] [--single-iteration]  - Run daemon loop\n│   ├── status                   - List daemon tasks with lease info\n│   ├── abort <TASK_ID>          - Abort claimed/active task\n│   ├── retry <TASK_ID>          - Retry failed task\n│   └── reconcile [--ttl-seconds N]  - Cleanup stale leases\n└── conformance\n    ├── list                     - List all scenarios\n    └── run [--filter <PATTERN>] - Execute conformance tests\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. FLOW PRESET DEFINITIONS\n\n**4 Built-In Flows** (defined in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs`):\n\n**1. Standard Flow** (`standard`)\n- Stages (8): PromptReview → Planning → Implementation → Qa → Review → CompletionPanel → AcceptanceQa → FinalReview\n- Validation Profile: \"standard-default\" with final review enabled\n- Remediation Triggers: Qa, Review\n- Late Stages: CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview\n- Best For: Full feature delivery with comprehensive validation\n\n**2. Quick Dev Flow** (`quick_dev`)\n- Stages (4): PlanAndImplement → Review → ApplyFixes → FinalReview\n- Validation Profile: \"quick-dev-default\" with final review enabled\n- Remediation Triggers: Review\n- Late Stages: FinalReview\n- Best For: Small code changes, bug fixes\n\n**3. Docs Change Flow** (`docs_change`)\n- Stages (4): DocsPlan → DocsUpdate → DocsValidation → Review\n- Validation Profile: \"docs-default\" with final review disabled\n- Remediation Triggers: DocsValidation, Review\n- Late Stages: (none)\n- Best For: Documentation updates\n\n**4. CI Improvement Flow** (`ci_improvement`)\n- Stages (4): CiPlan → CiUpdate → CiValidation → Review\n- Validation Profile: \"ci-default\" with final review disabled\n- Remediation Triggers: CiValidation, Review\n- Late Stages: (none)\n- Best For: CI/CD automation changes\n\n---\n\n### 6. ALL STAGE DEFINITIONS\n\n**16 Total Stages** (enum `StageId`):\n\n**Standard Flow Stages**:\n- `prompt_review` - Human review of requirements\n- `planning` - Design & approach\n- `implementation` - Code changes\n- `qa` - Quality testing\n- `review` - Code review\n- `completion_panel` - Completion validation\n- `acceptance_qa` - Final QA\n- `final_review` - Final human sign-off\n\n**Quick Dev Stages**:\n- `plan_and_implement` - Combined planning & coding\n- `apply_fixes` - Remediation after review\n\n**Docs Flow Stages**:\n- `docs_plan` - Documentation planning\n- `docs_update` - Content updates\n- `docs_validation` - Verification\n\n**CI Flow Stages**:\n- `ci_plan` - Automation planning\n- `ci_update` - Configuration updates\n- `ci_validation` - Testing automation\n\n---\n\n### 7. CONFORMANCE TEST STRUCTURE (18 Test Suites)\n\nLocated under `tests/conformance/features/` (Cucumber feature files):\n\n**Workspace Tests**:\n- `workspace_init.feature` - Workspace initialization\n- `workspace_config.feature` - Configuration management\n\n**Flow Tests**:\n- `flow_discovery.feature` - List/show flows\n\n**Project Tests**:\n- `active_project.feature` - Active project selection\n- `project_records.feature` - Create/list/show/delete projects\n\n**Run Execution Tests**:\n- `run_start_standard.feature` - Standard flow execution\n- `run_start_quick_dev.feature` - Quick dev flow execution\n- `run_start_docs_change.feature` - Docs change flow execution\n- `run_start_ci_improvement.feature` - CI improvement flow execution\n\n**Run State Management Tests**:\n- `run_queries.feature` - Status/history/tail queries\n- `run_completion_rounds.feature` - Completion round logic\n- `run_resume_non_standard.feature` - Resume from paused/failed\n- `run_resume_retry.feature` - Retry failed stages\n- `run_rollback.feature` - Rollback to earlier stages\n\n**Daemon Tests**:\n- `daemon_lifecycle.feature` - Daemon start/status/abort/retry\n- `daemon_routing.feature` - Task routing to worktrees\n\n**Behavioral Tests**:\n- `stage_contracts.feature` - Stage invocation contracts\n- `requirements_drafting.feature` - Requirements gathering workflow\n\n**Total Scenarios**: ~80+ scenarios covering end-to-end workflows\n\n---\n\n### 8. SHARED DOMAIN TYPES\n\n**Core Types** (`src/shared/domain.rs`):\n- `FlowPreset` (enum) - 4 preset choices\n- `StageId` (enum) - 16 stage definitions\n- `FailureClass` (enum) - 6 failure categories (Transport, SchemaValidation, DomainValidation, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailed)\n- `BackendFamily` (enum) - 4 backend families (Claude, Codex, OpenRouter, Stub)\n- `BackendSpec` - Backend capabilities\n- `CapabilityMetadata` - Feature support matrix\n- `WorkspaceConfig` - V1 workspace configuration\n- `ProjectId` - Valid project identifier\n\n**Error Types** (`src/shared/error.rs`):\n- 30+ error variants covering workspace, project, run, daemon, and conformance failures\n- Structured error messages with context\n\n---\n\n### 9. TESTING INFRASTRUCTURE\n\n**Unit Tests** (`tests/unit/` - 21 test files):\n- `active_project_test.rs`\n- `adapter_contract_test.rs`\n- `agent_execution_test.rs`\n- `automation_runtime_test.rs`\n- `config_test.rs`\n- `conformance_spec_test.rs`\n- `domain_test.rs`\n- `flow_preset_test.rs` / `flow_semantics_test.rs`\n- `journal_test.rs`\n- `project_run_record_test.rs`\n- `query_test.rs`\n- `renderer_test.rs`\n- `requirements_drafting_test.rs`\n- `retry_policy_test.rs`\n- `rollback_test.rs`\n- `stage_contract_test.rs`\n- `stub_backend_test.rs`\n- `workflow_engine_test.rs`\n- `workspace_test.rs`\n\n**CLI Integration Tests** (`tests/cli.rs`):\n- ~1,500 lines of test helpers and fixtures\n- Workspace initialization fixtures\n- Project creation fixtures\n- Active project selection\n- Editor script injection for config testing\n\n---\n\n### 10. KEY ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS\n\n**1. Bounded Contexts (DDD)**\n- Each context has clear boundaries and ports\n- Ports define contracts; adapters implement\n\n**2. Adapter Pattern**\n- Filesystem, stub backend, worktree are swappable\n- Test injection seams via environment variables\n\n**3. Cycle-Based Execution**\n- Stages run in cycles\n- Failed stages trigger remediation cycles\n- Completion rounds track multi-cycle progress\n\n**4. Journaling & Snapshots**\n- All state changes logged to immutable journal (NDJSON)\n- Point-in-time snapshots for fast queries\n- Supports rollback via checkpoint restoration\n\n**5. Lease-Based Concurrency**\n- Daemon acquires leases on worktrees\n- Prevents concurrent edits\n- Heartbeat-based stale lease detection\n\n**6. Test Seams**\n- Stub backend with injectable payloads\n- Environment variable overrides for failure modes\n- Feature-flagged test-only behavior\n\n---\n\n### 11. IMPLEMENTATION STATUS\n\n**Completed**:\n- All 8 CLI commands fully functional\n- 6 bounded contexts with ports and adapters\n- 4 flow presets with stage orchestration\n- Workspace initialization and configuration\n- Project lifecycle management\n- Run execution with state persistence\n- Daemon task processing and routing\n- Conformance test framework\n- Comprehensive error handling\n- Session management and reuse\n\n**Not Yet Implemented**:\n- Real LLM backend integrations (only stub)\n- Persistent daemon heartbeat/monitoring\n- Full Git integration (partial worktree support)\n\n---\n\n### FILE PATHS - KEY LOCATIONS\n\n**src/contexts/**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/`\n\n**src/adapters/**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/stub_backend.rs`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/worktree.rs`\n\n**src/cli/**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/` (8 command modules)\n\n**tests/**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/` (18 feature files)\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/` (21 unit test files)\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs` (integration tests)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a91c4fa446178179b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63680\ntool_uses: 46\nduration_ms: 92493</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2cdec833-d9a4-4fe7-8fdf-432611cd39d7","uuid":"c10d4c28-3acf-4776-bfa8-fd66a7d5a096","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the ralph-burning-rewrite directory thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - list all directories under src/\n2. All bounded contexts under src/contexts/ \n3. All adapter modules under src/adapters/\n4. The CLI command structure (look at main.rs and any CLI modules)\n5. All flow preset definitions\n6. The conformance test structure under tests/\n\nBe very thorough - I need a complete picture of what's implemented.","agentId":"a91c4fa446178179b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed report of the entire project structure.\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE EXPLORATION REPORT: ralph-burning-rewrite\n\nI've thoroughly explored the ralph-burning-rewrite project. Here's a complete picture of what's implemented:\n\n---\n\n### 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE - src/ DIRECTORIES\n\nThe project is organized into 5 main directories under `src/`:\n\n**`src/cli/`** - CLI Command Handlers (8 modules)\n- `init.rs` - Initialize workspace\n- `flow.rs` - List/show flow presets\n- `config.rs` - Manage workspace configuration\n- `project.rs` - Create/select/list/delete/show projects\n- `run.rs` - Start/resume/status/history/tail/rollback runs\n- `requirements.rs` - Draft requirements, answer questions\n- `daemon.rs` - Manage automation daemon (start, status, abort, retry, reconcile)\n- `conformance.rs` - Run conformance tests\n- `mod.rs` - CLI routing (8 commands)\n\n**`src/contexts/`** - 6 Bounded Contexts (DDD architecture)\n- `agent_execution/` - AI backend invocation\n- `automation_runtime/` - Daemon-based task execution\n- `conformance_spec/` - Behavioral test specifications\n- `project_run_record/` - Workflow execution state management\n- `requirements_drafting/` - Interactive requirements gathering\n- `workflow_composition/` - Flow definitions and orchestration\n- `workspace_governance/` - Workspace initialization and config\n\n**`src/adapters/`** - Infrastructure Adapters (4 modules)\n- `fs.rs` - Filesystem-based storage (15 store implementations)\n- `stub_backend.rs` - In-memory AI backend for testing\n- `worktree.rs` - Git worktree management\n- `mod.rs` - Module declaration\n\n**`src/shared/`** - Shared Kernel\n- `domain.rs` - Core domain types\n- `error.rs` - Error handling\n- `mod.rs` - Module declaration\n\n---\n\n### 2. BOUNDED CONTEXTS - DETAILED VIEW\n\n#### **agent_execution** - AI Backend Execution\nFiles: `model.rs`, `service.rs`, `session.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Abstract layer for LLM backend invocations\n- **Key Types**:\n  - `InvocationContract` - Stage execution contract\n  - `InvocationPayload` - Stage input/output data\n  - `AgentExecutionService` - Executes stage invocations\n  - `SessionManager` - Manages LLM session reuse\n- **Features**:\n  - Backend selection (Claude, Codex, OpenRouter, Stub)\n  - Structured output validation\n  - Raw output capture\n  - Session persistence\n\n#### **automation_runtime** - Daemon-Based Task Processing\nFiles: `daemon_loop.rs`, `lease_service.rs`, `model.rs`, `routing.rs`, `task_service.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Long-running daemon that claims and processes tasks\n- **Key Types**:\n  - `DaemonTask` - Task with status, lease, and metadata\n  - `WorktreeLease` - Git worktree ownership tracking\n  - `DaemonLoop` - Main polling loop\n  - `LeaseService` - Lease management and reconciliation\n  - `RoutingEngine` - Route tasks to worktrees\n- **Task Statuses**: Pending → Claimed → Active → (Completed/Failed/Aborted)\n- **Ports**:\n  - `DaemonStorePort` - Task and lease persistence\n  - `WorktreePort` - Git worktree operations\n\n#### **conformance_spec** - Behavioral Test Framework\nFiles: `catalog.rs`, `cutover_guard.rs`, `model.rs`, `runner.rs`, `scenarios.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Cucumber-based conformance test execution\n- **Key Components**:\n  - Feature file discovery from `tests/conformance/features/`\n  - Scenario registration and filtering\n  - Test runner with reporter\n  - Cutover guard validation\n\n#### **project_run_record** - Run State Management\nFiles: `journal.rs`, `model.rs`, `queries.rs`, `service.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Durable state tracking for workflow execution\n- **Key Types**:\n  - `ProjectRecord` - Canonical project metadata\n  - `RunSnapshot` - Current execution state\n  - `JournalEvent` - Immutable event log\n  - `Payload` - Stage input/output artifacts\n  - `RollbackPoint` - Checkpoint for recovery\n- **Ports**:\n  - `ProjectStorePort` - Project metadata persistence\n  - `RunSnapshotPort` - Execution state queries/writes\n  - `JournalStorePort` - Event log persistence\n  - `ArtifactStorePort` - Payload/artifact storage\n\n#### **requirements_drafting** - Interactive Requirements\nFiles: `contracts.rs`, `model.rs`, `renderers.rs`, `service.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Gather requirements through Q&A dialogue\n- **Key Types**:\n  - `QuestionSet` - Multiple choice/open questions\n  - `AnswerCollection` - User responses\n  - `ProjectSeed` - Generated project template\n- **Modes**: Draft (interactive), Quick (automated with stub)\n- **Output**: Generates seed prompt and project configuration\n\n#### **workflow_composition** - Flow Orchestration\nFiles: `contracts.rs`, `engine.rs`, `payloads.rs`, `renderers.rs`, `retry_policy.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Define and execute multi-stage workflows\n- **Key Concepts**:\n  - `FlowDefinition` - Stage sequence + validation profile\n  - `FlowSemantics` - Flow-specific logic (planning, execution, remediation)\n  - `RetryPolicy` - Failure recovery strategy\n  - Cycle-based execution (multiple attempts through remediation)\n  - Amendment queue for deferred changes\n- **Main Functions**:\n  - `execute_run()` - Run all stages from start\n  - `resume_run()` - Resume from failed/paused state\n  - Cycle management and completion rounds\n\n#### **workspace_governance** - Configuration & Initialization\nFiles: `config.rs`, `mod.rs`\n- **Purpose**: Workspace and project configuration management\n- **Key Features**:\n  - Workspace initialization with version 1\n  - Config loading/saving (TOML-based)\n  - Active project tracking\n  - Configuration keys: `prompt_review.enabled`, `default_flow`, `default_backend`, `default_model`\n- **Directory Structure**:\n  ```\n  .ralph-burning/\n    workspace.toml\n    active-project\n    projects/{project-id}/\n      project.toml\n      prompt.md\n      run.json\n      journal.ndjson\n      sessions.json\n      history/{payloads,artifacts}/\n      runtime/{logs,backend,temp}/\n      amendments/\n      rollback/\n    requirements/\n    daemon/\n      tasks/\n      leases/\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### 3. ADAPTER MODULES - IMPLEMENTATIONS\n\n#### **fs.rs** (1,538 lines) - Filesystem Storage Adapters\nImplements 15 store ports for durable storage:\n\n**Project Management Stores**:\n- `FsProjectStore` - ProjectStorePort\n- `FsActiveProjectStore` - ActiveProjectPort\n\n**Execution State Stores**:\n- `FsRunSnapshotStore` - RunSnapshotPort (read-only)\n- `FsRunSnapshotWriteStore` - RunSnapshotWritePort\n- `FsJournalStore` - JournalStorePort\n\n**Payload & Artifact Stores**:\n- `FsArtifactStore` - ArtifactStorePort\n- `FsPayloadArtifactWriteStore` - PayloadArtifactWritePort\n- `FsRollbackPointStore` - RollbackPointStorePort\n\n**Backend Output Stores**:\n- `FsRawOutputStore` - RawOutputPort\n- `FsSessionStore` - SessionStorePort\n- `FsRuntimeLogStore` - RuntimeLogStorePort\n- `FsRuntimeLogWriteStore` - RuntimeLogWritePort\n\n**Daemon Stores**:\n- `FsDaemonStore` - DaemonStorePort (tasks, leases, journal, locks)\n- `FsAmendmentQueueStore` - AmendmentQueuePort\n\n**Requirements Stores**:\n- `FsRequirementsStore` - RequirementsStorePort\n\n**FileSystem Utilities**:\n- Static methods for: workspace init, TOML rendering, file I/O, editor invocation\n\n#### **stub_backend.rs** (414 lines) - Test AI Backend\n- In-memory LLM simulation for testing\n- Environment variable injection seams for failure modes:\n  - `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_BACKEND_UNAVAILABLE` - Simulate unavailable backend\n  - `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_FAIL_INVOKE_STAGE` - Fail specific stage invocation\n  - `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_TRANSIENT_FAILURE` - Transient N-attempt failures\n  - `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_STAGE_OVERRIDES` - Custom payloads per stage\n  - `RALPH_BURNING_TEST_LABEL_OVERRIDES` - Custom requirement responses\n\n#### **worktree.rs** (198 lines) - Git Worktree Management\n- Create/remove worktrees in `.ralph-burning/daemon/worktrees/{task-id}/`\n- Branch naming based on task ID\n- Rebase onto default branch\n- Shell-based git operations\n\n---\n\n### 4. CLI COMMAND STRUCTURE\n\n**Main CLI (defined in `src/cli/mod.rs`)**:\n\n```\nralph-burning [SUBCOMMAND]\n├── init                         - Initialize workspace\n├── flow\n│   ├── list                     - List all flow presets\n│   └── show <flow_id>           - Show flow details\n├── config\n│   ├── show                     - Display all configuration\n│   ├── get <key>                - Get single config value\n│   ├── set <key> <value>        - Set config value\n│   └── edit                     - Edit workspace.toml in editor\n├── project\n│   ├── create --id <ID> --name <NAME> --prompt <PATH> --flow <FLOW>\n│   ├── select <ID>              - Set active project\n│   ├── list                     - List all projects\n│   ├── show [<ID>]              - Show project details (active if not specified)\n│   └── delete <ID>              - Delete project\n├── run\n│   ├── start                    - Execute all stages of active project\n│   ├── resume                   - Resume from failed/paused snapshot\n│   ├── status                   - Show current execution status\n│   ├── history                  - Show all journal events and payloads\n│   ├── tail [--logs]            - Show recent events and optional runtime logs\n│   └── rollback --to <STAGE> [--hard]  - Rollback to stage\n├── requirements\n│   ├── draft --idea <IDEA>      - Interactive requirements gathering\n│   ├── quick --idea <IDEA>      - Automated requirements (stub backend)\n│   ├── show <RUN_ID>            - Display requirements result\n│   └── answer <RUN_ID>          - Submit answers to pending questions\n├── daemon\n│   ├── start [--poll-seconds N] [--single-iteration]  - Run daemon loop\n│   ├── status                   - List daemon tasks with lease info\n│   ├── abort <TASK_ID>          - Abort claimed/active task\n│   ├── retry <TASK_ID>          - Retry failed task\n│   └── reconcile [--ttl-seconds N]  - Cleanup stale leases\n└── conformance\n    ├── list                     - List all scenarios\n    └── run [--filter <PATTERN>] - Execute conformance tests\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. FLOW PRESET DEFINITIONS\n\n**4 Built-In Flows** (defined in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs`):\n\n**1. Standard Flow** (`standard`)\n- Stages (8): PromptReview → Planning → Implementation → Qa → Review → CompletionPanel → AcceptanceQa → FinalReview\n- Validation Profile: \"standard-default\" with final review enabled\n- Remediation Triggers: Qa, Review\n- Late Stages: CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview\n- Best For: Full feature delivery with comprehensive validation\n\n**2. Quick Dev Flow** (`quick_dev`)\n- Stages (4): PlanAndImplement → Review → ApplyFixes → FinalReview\n- Validation Profile: \"quick-dev-default\" with final review enabled\n- Remediation Triggers: Review\n- Late Stages: FinalReview\n- Best For: Small code changes, bug fixes\n\n**3. Docs Change Flow** (`docs_change`)\n- Stages (4): DocsPlan → DocsUpdate → DocsValidation → Review\n- Validation Profile: \"docs-default\" with final review disabled\n- Remediation Triggers: DocsValidation, Review\n- Late Stages: (none)\n- Best For: Documentation updates\n\n**4. CI Improvement Flow** (`ci_improvement`)\n- Stages (4): CiPlan → CiUpdate → CiValidation → Review\n- Validation Profile: \"ci-default\" with final review disabled\n- Remediation Triggers: CiValidation, Review\n- Late Stages: (none)\n- Best For: CI/CD automation changes\n\n---\n\n### 6. ALL STAGE DEFINITIONS\n\n**16 Total Stages** (enum `StageId`):\n\n**Standard Flow Stages**:\n- `prompt_review` - Human review of requirements\n- `planning` - Design & approach\n- `implementation` - Code changes\n- `qa` - Quality testing\n- `review` - Code review\n- `completion_panel` - Completion validation\n- `acceptance_qa` - Final QA\n- `final_review` - Final human sign-off\n\n**Quick Dev Stages**:\n- `plan_and_implement` - Combined planning & coding\n- `apply_fixes` - Remediation after review\n\n**Docs Flow Stages**:\n- `docs_plan` - Documentation planning\n- `docs_update` - Content updates\n- `docs_validation` - Verification\n\n**CI Flow Stages**:\n- `ci_plan` - Automation planning\n- `ci_update` - Configuration updates\n- `ci_validation` - Testing automation\n\n---\n\n### 7. CONFORMANCE TEST STRUCTURE (18 Test Suites)\n\nLocated under `tests/conformance/features/` (Cucumber feature files):\n\n**Workspace Tests**:\n- `workspace_init.feature` - Workspace initialization\n- `workspace_config.feature` - Configuration management\n\n**Flow Tests**:\n- `flow_discovery.feature` - List/show flows\n\n**Project Tests**:\n- `active_project.feature` - Active project selection\n- `project_records.feature` - Create/list/show/delete projects\n\n**Run Execution Tests**:\n- `run_start_standard.feature` - Standard flow execution\n- `run_start_quick_dev.feature` - Quick dev flow execution\n- `run_start_docs_change.feature` - Docs change flow execution\n- `run_start_ci_improvement.feature` - CI improvement flow execution\n\n**Run State Management Tests**:\n- `run_queries.feature` - Status/history/tail queries\n- `run_completion_rounds.feature` - Completion round logic\n- `run_resume_non_standard.feature` - Resume from paused/failed\n- `run_resume_retry.feature` - Retry failed stages\n- `run_rollback.feature` - Rollback to earlier stages\n\n**Daemon Tests**:\n- `daemon_lifecycle.feature` - Daemon start/status/abort/retry\n- `daemon_routing.feature` - Task routing to worktrees\n\n**Behavioral Tests**:\n- `stage_contracts.feature` - Stage invocation contracts\n- `requirements_drafting.feature` - Requirements gathering workflow\n\n**Total Scenarios**: ~80+ scenarios covering end-to-end workflows\n\n---\n\n### 8. SHARED DOMAIN TYPES\n\n**Core Types** (`src/shared/domain.rs`):\n- `FlowPreset` (enum) - 4 preset choices\n- `StageId` (enum) - 16 stage definitions\n- `FailureClass` (enum) - 6 failure categories (Transport, SchemaValidation, DomainValidation, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailed)\n- `BackendFamily` (enum) - 4 backend families (Claude, Codex, OpenRouter, Stub)\n- `BackendSpec` - Backend capabilities\n- `CapabilityMetadata` - Feature support matrix\n- `WorkspaceConfig` - V1 workspace configuration\n- `ProjectId` - Valid project identifier\n\n**Error Types** (`src/shared/error.rs`):\n- 30+ error variants covering workspace, project, run, daemon, and conformance failures\n- Structured error messages with context\n\n---\n\n### 9. TESTING INFRASTRUCTURE\n\n**Unit Tests** (`tests/unit/` - 21 test files):\n- `active_project_test.rs`\n- `adapter_contract_test.rs`\n- `agent_execution_test.rs`\n- `automation_runtime_test.rs`\n- `config_test.rs`\n- `conformance_spec_test.rs`\n- `domain_test.rs`\n- `flow_preset_test.rs` / `flow_semantics_test.rs`\n- `journal_test.rs`\n- `project_run_record_test.rs`\n- `query_test.rs`\n- `renderer_test.rs`\n- `requirements_drafting_test.rs`\n- `retry_policy_test.rs`\n- `rollback_test.rs`\n- `stage_contract_test.rs`\n- `stub_backend_test.rs`\n- `workflow_engine_test.rs`\n- `workspace_test.rs`\n\n**CLI Integration Tests** (`tests/cli.rs`):\n- ~1,500 lines of test helpers and fixtures\n- Workspace initialization fixtures\n- Project creation fixtures\n- Active project selection\n- Editor script injection for config testing\n\n---\n\n### 10. KEY ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS\n\n**1. Bounded Contexts (DDD)**\n- Each context has clear boundaries and ports\n- Ports define contracts; adapters implement\n\n**2. Adapter Pattern**\n- Filesystem, stub backend, worktree are swappable\n- Test injection seams via environment variables\n\n**3. Cycle-Based Execution**\n- Stages run in cycles\n- Failed stages trigger remediation cycles\n- Completion rounds track multi-cycle progress\n\n**4. Journaling & Snapshots**\n- All state changes logged to immutable journal (NDJSON)\n- Point-in-time snapshots for fast queries\n- Supports rollback via checkpoint restoration\n\n**5. Lease-Based Concurrency**\n- Daemon acquires leases on worktrees\n- Prevents concurrent edits\n- Heartbeat-based stale lease detection\n\n**6. Test Seams**\n- Stub backend with injectable payloads\n- Environment variable overrides for failure modes\n- Feature-flagged test-only behavior\n\n---\n\n### 11. IMPLEMENTATION STATUS\n\n**Completed**:\n- All 8 CLI commands fully functional\n- 6 bounded contexts with ports and adapters\n- 4 flow presets with stage orchestration\n- Workspace initialization and configuration\n- Project lifecycle management\n- Run execution with state persistence\n- Daemon task processing and routing\n- Conformance test framework\n- Comprehensive error handling\n- Session management and reuse\n\n**Not Yet Implemented**:\n- Real LLM backend integrations (only stub)\n- Persistent daemon heartbeat/monitoring\n- Full Git integration (partial worktree support)\n\n---\n\n### FILE PATHS - KEY LOCATIONS\n\n**src/contexts/**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/`\n- `/root/new-ra