{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CbvMMytrEsep8F3HzfNTmM","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive verification report.\n\n## Storage Layout Verification Report\n\nI have completed a comprehensive verification of the ralph-burning-rewrite filesystem adapter against Section 6 (Acceptance Criteria) of the requirements specification. Here are my findings:\n\n### DIRECTORY STRUCTURE VERIFICATION\n\nThe implemented filesystem layout in `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` correctly matches the required storage structure from the spec:\n\n**Workspace Root: `.ralph-burning/`**\n- `workspace.toml` - Created via `FileSystem::create_workspace()` at line 60\n- `active-project` - Managed via `read_active_project()` and `write_active_project()` at lines 110-128\n\n**Projects: `.ralph-burning/projects/<project-id>/`**\nAll files implemented at lines 385-450:\n- `project.toml` - Project configuration\n- `prompt.md` - Prompt file\n- `run.json` - Run snapshot\n- `journal.ndjson` - Event journal\n- `sessions.json` - Session store\n- **Subdirectories** (const PROJECT_SUBDIRS at lines 36-44):\n  - `history/payloads/*` - Payload history\n  - `history/artifacts/*` - Artifact history\n  - `runtime/logs/*` - Runtime logs\n  - `runtime/backend/*` - Backend data\n  - `runtime/temp/*` - Temporary files\n  - `amendments/*` - Amendment storage (lines 897, 904, 947, 956, 974)\n  - `rollback/*` - Rollback points (lines 711-756)\n\n**Requirements: `.ralph-burning/requirements/<requirements-run-id>/`**\nAll files implemented at lines 1269-1532:\n- `run.json` - Requirements run state (lines 1269-1273)\n- `journal.ndjson` - Requirements journal (lines 1292-1329)\n- `answers.toml` - Answer template (lines 1430-1432)\n- `answers.json` - Parsed answers (lines 1440-1458)\n- `seed/project.json` - Project seed (lines 1460-1492)\n- `seed/prompt.md` - Prompt seed (lines 1460-1492)\n- `sessions.json` - Session store (lines 1240-1245)\n- **Subdirectories** (const REQUIREMENTS_RUN_SUBDIRS at lines 1220-1227):\n  - `history/payloads/*` - Payload history (lines 1331-1342)\n  - `history/artifacts/*` - Artifact history (lines 1345-1355)\n  - `runtime/logs/*` - Runtime logs\n  - `runtime/backend/*` - Backend data\n  - `runtime/temp/*` - Temporary files (lines 1387-1388)\n  - `seed/` - Seed directory (line 1226)\n\n**Daemon: `.ralph-burning/daemon/`**\nImplemented at lines 1008-1180:\n- `journal.ndjson` - Daemon journal (line 1038)\n- **Subdirectories**:\n  - `tasks/*` - Task storage (lines 1017-1018, 1060-1087)\n  - `leases/*` - Lease storage (lines 1021-1022, 1090-1133)\n\n### JOURNAL.NDJSON AS AUTHORITATIVE EVENT SOURCE\n\n**Verified Correct:** journal.ndjson is the authoritative event source for requirements, NOT artifact scans.\n\n**Evidence from code:**\n\n1. **`show()` method** (lines 348-403):\n   - Line 348 documentation explicitly states: \"Derives its read model from `run.json` and `journal.ndjson`, not by scanning artifacts.\"\n   - Line 352: `let journal = self.store.read_journal(base_dir, run_id)?;`\n   - Journal events (not artifact scans) drive the state display\n\n2. **Journal-first persistence pattern** throughout service.rs:\n   - `append_journal_event()` is called (lines 150-158, 217-225, 269-277, etc.) BEFORE stage progression\n   - Line 210 comment: \"journal immediately after the payload/artifact pair succeeds\"\n   - Lines 484-500: Answer submission journals event before updating run state\n   - Lines 581-601: Draft generation journals event before downstream operations\n\n3. **No artifact scanning**:\n   - Grep results show documentation at lines 249 and 349 explicitly note \"not scanning artifacts\"\n   - All state derivation uses `read_journal()`, `read_run()`, `read_answers_json()`, and explicit payload reads\n   - No directory traversal or artifact discovery mechanism\n\n### ATOMIC WRIT